1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
=== kisskh.xyz===

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,740
[All characters, behaviors, locations,
organizations, professions, and events

3
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:07,490
shown in this series are entirely fictional,
created solely for entertainment purposes,

4
00:00:07,510 --> 00:00:11,250
with no intention of instructing
or endorsing any kind of behaviors;

5
00:00:11,270 --> 00:00:15,000
viewer discretion is advised]

6
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:25,640
[I'm here. Where are you?]

7
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:30,760
Hey, wait!

8
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:34,780
I'm so sorry,
but the promotional room you booked

9
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:36,240
is fully booked for tonight.

10
00:00:36,260 --> 00:00:39,100
We are actually partnered with
a resort up the hill.

11
00:00:39,120 --> 00:00:41,140
It's called 'Phusangdao.'

12
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:43,960
It only starts at 400 baht a night.

13
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:45,860
That's it.

14
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:48,580
[3KY 3177, Chiang Rai]

15
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:51,800
[2KY 9969, Chiang Rai]

16
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:53,880
Shit!

17
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:04,959
I wonder where your mind
is drifting off to.

18
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:06,080
Boss.

19
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:09,000
I'm sorry.

20
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,440
I'm feeling a bit tired today.

21
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:13,600
I've been having headaches nonstop.

22
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:15,480
Whoa! Whoa!

23
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,300
This only hurts your name, Boss.

24
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:19,160
Someone like you

25
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:20,520
really gets tired from...

26
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:23,280
- Hey, know your boundaries.
- Ow!

27
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:25,539
I'm not talking about that.

28
00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:27,120
I know, Boss.

29
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:29,520
You are Boss Sila, after all.

30
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:33,160
You are resilient, tenacious,
and tough as a rock.

31
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,960
Boss, are you still concerned
about last night's deal?

32
00:01:50,479 --> 00:01:52,360
You look rather stressed out.

33
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:55,160
You have been frowning
ever since we set off.

34
00:01:56,520 --> 00:01:58,520
I'm not particularly
concerned about the deal.

35
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:02,200
It's likely to go well.

36
00:02:03,420 --> 00:02:05,780
What I'm concerned about
is the farm workers.

37
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,720
The farm workload has increased lately.

38
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:12,240
The elderly who have
been with us for so long

39
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,280
are now struggling
to keep up with the work,

40
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:17,200
and the younger generation
is not interested in working here.

41
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:20,320
I'm genuinely concerned that
we won't have enough manpower.

42
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:24,160
I've already somewhat
discussed this with Ms. Wipa, Boss.

43
00:02:25,380 --> 00:02:28,120
We still have time to deal with
the manpower issue,

44
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:31,200
as our yields are still meeting
the required standards,

45
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:33,480
and even exceeding them
on some occasions, Boss.

46
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:40,160
How can I actually repay them?

47
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,200
I hope this massive deal

48
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,480
can be a gift for them.

49
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:58,320
Uh, Boss.

50
00:02:58,660 --> 00:02:59,880
Is that

51
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:01,640
Ms. Mueanphae?

52
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,260
Hey! Don't say that.

53
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,140
I won't let you off the hook.

54
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,220
Neither will I.

55
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:08,860
- Chakkrit, stop the car.
- Yes, Boss.

56
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,660
- It's so obvious.
- Alright. Bring it.

57
00:03:10,680 --> 00:03:12,500
- Don't shut up now, alright?
- Don't worry, I won't.

58
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:14,340
Yeah, call everyone. Bring them all here.

59
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,420
Keep talking.

60
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:17,020
Of course. I'm not in the wrong anyway.

61
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:18,220
You are the one at fault.

62
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,000
No, you.

63
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:20,579
- I'm not backing down.
- Neither am I.

64
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,440
- Call them. Bring whoever you called here.
- What's going on here?

65
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:24,520
Sila?

66
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:35,920
Perfect timing.

67
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:37,980
This is perfect.

68
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,720
You can vouch for me that

69
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,280
this tofu-looking guy

70
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:43,460
rear-ended my Maple Syrup.

71
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:45,960
Did you get hurt? Are you okay?

72
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,579
I'm fine,

73
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,180
but the trunk...

74
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:51,480
Gosh! You!

75
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:54,180
I told you that
you abruptly stopped the car.

76
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,280
See? Sila?

77
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,500
- He just won't shut up.
- Okay, Phae.

78
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,480
Calm down, alright?

79
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,980
I'll take care of this myself.

80
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:04,140
What about the fruits for your mother?

81
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:06,360
It's fine.
You can bring them to her next time.

82
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,160
I'll have Chakkrit
drive you to your destination.

83
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,880
And the cost, I'll take care of it, okay?

84
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,200
Okay.

85
00:04:14,380 --> 00:04:15,600
This way, Ms. Mueanphae.

86
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,440
Oh!

87
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:19,720
So your name is Phae?

88
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,240
- Where are you going, Prickly Phae?
- What?

89
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:22,019
Ms. Mueanphae.

90
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:23,860
- Come back and settle this!
- Hey, now.

91
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:25,000
- So what will it be?!
- Hey!

92
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,200
Please stop.

93
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:36,800
What is it? Why must you step in?

94
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:41,440
I'll take care of all the damage,

95
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:43,240
so don't worry, okay?

96
00:04:44,260 --> 00:04:45,240
Take care of what?

97
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:47,320
Do we know each other,
interfering like this?

98
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:49,280
Yes, we do.

99
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,000
I think I do know you.

100
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,740
Just take off the hood.

101
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,560
I already know who you are.

102
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:58,800
Come on.

103
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,040
I'm not wearing it
as a disguise or anything.

104
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,160
You see?

105
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:04,460
The sunlight is so bright out here.

106
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:06,520
I was worried I'd get skin cancer.

107
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:12,360
About the compensation
that Phae demanded,

108
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,400
I'll take care of it myself, no worries.

109
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,760
Right...

110
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:19,920
You probably know
each other well, don't you?

111
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,120
No wonder.

112
00:05:22,060 --> 00:05:23,860
One loves to cause a scene,

113
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,280
while the other

114
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,160
- loves to be so damn nosy.
- Hey, you!

115
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,840
Could you be civil for a second?

116
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,820
Do you think I'm stepping in

117
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,159
just so I can screw
a tourist like you over?

118
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:36,460
I'm only doing this
so it doesn't get out of hand,

119
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,200
and I also want to help her.

120
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,080
This is a rental car, isn't it?

121
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:43,240
Do you know how much
Mueanphae's car repair cost?

122
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,620
What? You want to flex, don't you?

123
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:46,940
You think I can't
afford to pay for it, huh?

124
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:48,040
Well, can you?

125
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:51,280
The total cost for your rental car insurance
and her car repair cost

126
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:53,280
should be

127
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:55,640
400,000 baht, give or take.

128
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:57,920
Now, do you think you can pay them?

129
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:59,560
- Yes, 400,000 baht.
- Mm.

130
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:02,000
- Give me a moment.
- No problem. I can wait.

131
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:08,760
[Current balance: 23,000 baht]

132
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:13,640
So?

133
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:15,520
Listen.

134
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:19,880
Can I pay in installments?

135
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,600
Or do you accept credit cards?

136
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:23,720
Hey.

137
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:26,280
Do I look like a cashier to you?

138
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,880
If you don't have the money,

139
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,720
you'll have to pay
for it in some other way.

140
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,040
Are you interested?

141
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,220
Don't make it sound weird,

142
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:48,100
you pervert! Dirty-minded!

143
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,720
- You're such a...
- Now, now.

144
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,600
I'm asking you to work under me.

145
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,880
Where has your mind wandered off to?

146
00:06:56,670 --> 00:06:59,080
Who is the real pervert here?

147
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,040
Me working for you?

148
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:02,360
No way!

149
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,120
I live in Bangkok.

150
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,360
You want me to work for you?

151
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,420
I can't do that.

152
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:08,400
Then pay up.

153
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,520
Give me a moment, then.

154
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,200
So you finally called me?

155
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:20,800
I thought you'd already
blocked my number.

156
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:22,680
What is it?
What have you done this time?

157
00:07:22,780 --> 00:07:25,920
I knew you wouldn't make it out there.

158
00:07:26,020 --> 00:07:29,200
And don't be surprised that your credit cards
and bank accounts are empty.

159
00:07:29,340 --> 00:07:30,600
You've left the house, after all.

160
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:33,240
This means you can at least
make a living already, doesn't it?

161
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:38,280
And...

162
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:44,320
About the job you want me to do,

163
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:45,800
what is it?

164
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,720
[Phusangdao]
[Phusangdao Resort]

165
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:12,270
♫But no one sees what's behind my smiles♫

166
00:08:12,690 --> 00:08:16,330
♫It's the loneliness I try to hide♫

167
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:21,720
♫Will there be someone my heart's seeking?♫

168
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:25,590
♫Then today, I got you near♫

169
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:30,370
♫You made my heart drift away,♫

170
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,350
♫Lost in your gaze♫

171
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:35,830
♫Like a stream washing over me♫

172
00:08:35,860 --> 00:08:41,309
♫Wanna give this a try,
like it's more than one night?♫

173
00:08:41,340 --> 00:08:44,920
♫Let's change one night into♫

174
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,740
♫Something more, alright♫

175
00:08:46,780 --> 00:08:49,890
♫Let's follow our hearts once♫

176
00:08:49,950 --> 00:08:55,780
♫Wanna give this a try, just let me get inside?♫

177
00:08:55,840 --> 00:09:02,000
♫Deep inside, I'll make you feel whole♫

178
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:06,580
♫May I ask you to be my last?♫

179
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,000
Ow, Mok.

180
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,020
What the hell are you doing?

181
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,720
Can you stop being so fidgety?

182
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:29,120
No, this is how I pick tea leaves.

183
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:31,840
Sure, make sure you
pick a whole bunch of them.

184
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,120
We have to weigh our baskets soon.

185
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,920
If your yield is less than mine, you...

186
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,040
- What?
- Huh?!

187
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:42,480
How come you've already picked
this many tea leaves?

188
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:45,600
I saw you wandering about,
thinking you were slacking off.

189
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:47,400
Okay, fine.

190
00:09:47,540 --> 00:09:48,560
I can't lose now.

191
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,480
What's the rush, kiddo?

192
00:09:57,980 --> 00:09:59,280
I'm so upset.

193
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:03,200
I don't want to be treated
like a kid on the farm anymore.

194
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,160
When will I turn 20?

195
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,200
Damn it.

196
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:08,420
It's nice to be young.

197
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,760
Why do you want to grow up so badly?

198
00:10:09,940 --> 00:10:11,780
Yeah, easy for you to say.

199
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:13,160
You're already 20.

200
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:16,340
You can go to the pub and
hit on the girls there with Boss.

201
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,820
You just chose not to do it.

202
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:19,080
Why wait for me?

203
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:24,390
Hey, go there and tell me what it's like.

204
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,630
Please, Mok.

205
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,660
- Please, Mok.
- Hey.

206
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:29,320
See it for yourself if you're this curious.

207
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:32,160
Be patient, kiddo.

208
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,800
It's only a few months away

209
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,840
before it's your birthday.

210
00:10:36,420 --> 00:10:37,860
This 20-year-old bro

211
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:41,040
will be the one treating
his new 20-year-old bro himself.

212
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:43,080
What? You'll treat me?

213
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,560
- Yes.
- Treat me to what?

214
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:46,640
It's a secret.

215
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,520
Wait until it's your birthday.

216
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,560
Spill the beans, please, Mok.

217
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,080
Mok.

218
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,810
Please, spill it, Mok.

219
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:56,840
Please, Mok.

220
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:02,120
Damn it. I hope tomorrow is my birthday.

221
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:12,500
Oh, what the hell?

222
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:13,880
Hey!

223
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,520
Are you giving me your tea leaves?

224
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:16,920
Whoa!

225
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,520
- Mok!
- So heavy.

226
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,860
Hey, Mok!

227
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,100
You're giving me all of your harvest?

228
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,240
How generous of you.

229
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,760
Ugh, when are we getting there?

230
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:32,000
Fine. I'll get you for this someday.

231
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:34,720
Oh! Oh! Oh!

232
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,160
Hey, watch your step.

233
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,760
You're walking on grass,
not on a mall floor.

234
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:44,520
You're not helping me,

235
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,040
yet you still keep talking.

236
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,040
Shut up, you.

237
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,080
Oh, whoa!

238
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,820
It's always me...

239
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,600
What the hell?

240
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,160
It's not even my bad luck year yet.

241
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,800
Are the stars out of alignment?

242
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:03,480
Come.

243
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:04,560
Stop!

244
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,600
Stay there.

245
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,000
Let me. I'll handle this myself.

246
00:12:09,320 --> 00:12:10,440
What's wrong with you?

247
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:12,800
You complain when I'm not helping,
now you're telling me to stay away?

248
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:19,440
Hey, how far do we still have to go?

249
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,540
We're walking on grass.

250
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:21,620
It's hard to lug my luggage around.

251
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,940
And my arm is killing me,

252
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,360
as are my legs.

253
00:12:24,860 --> 00:12:26,200
Your car is under repair

254
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:28,720
because of someone's
carelessness, isn't it?

255
00:12:29,340 --> 00:12:31,320
That's why you have to
go on foot as punishment.

256
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:32,760
How many times must I repeat myself?

257
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,480
It's not my fault.

258
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:37,840
Driving here is already difficult enough,

259
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,600
and the entrance here is just a total mess.

260
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:43,840
I shouldn't have listened to
that receptionist to come here.

261
00:12:44,220 --> 00:12:45,640
I wonder

262
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,200
who the hell is running this place?

263
00:12:47,440 --> 00:12:49,760
I can't wait to see them.
I'll rate this place no stars.

264
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:52,920
Hello, Boss.

265
00:12:53,060 --> 00:12:54,180
Oh, hi.

266
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,480
Are you back?

267
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:56,320
Yes, I am.

268
00:12:56,740 --> 00:12:58,140
If you're done today,

269
00:12:58,180 --> 00:13:00,240
you can treat yourself
at the cafeteria before going home.

270
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:01,880
- Yes.
- You must be tired working all day.

271
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:03,740
Understood, Boss. If you'll excuse me.

272
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:04,360
No problem.

273
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:08,280
Hey.

274
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,280
You run this place?!

275
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,080
Yes.

276
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,400
My name is Sila,

277
00:13:18,740 --> 00:13:20,520
and this is Phusangdao Farm.

278
00:13:21,860 --> 00:13:23,520
What about you? What's your name?

279
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:25,260
Are you kidding me?

280
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,280
About what?

281
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:30,160
If it's me asking your name,

282
00:13:30,700 --> 00:13:31,920
then I wasn't kidding.

283
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:35,840
Saitharn.

284
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,560
My name is Saitharn.

285
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:43,360
What brings you to Chiang Rai, Saitharn?

286
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:48,960
None of your business.

287
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,800
Let's discuss the work
you want me to do here.

288
00:13:52,140 --> 00:13:53,240
What do I have to do?

289
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,960
How about I work at that resort?

290
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,600
I could be a receptionist.

291
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:00,700
I can speak English, too.

292
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,640
I can serve food,

293
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:02,920
manage parking...

294
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:06,200
No, not that one. The heat will kill me.

295
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,500
Then I'll go... indoor jobs,
working under a cold A/C,

296
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,520
I can do anything.

297
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:15,760
What?!

298
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:16,600
Hey, you!

299
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:17,620
Where are you going?

300
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,180
Aren't we supposed to go that way?

301
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:19,960
Hey!

302
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,200
Wait up!

303
00:14:23,160 --> 00:14:24,840
[Phusangdao Resort,
Phusangdao Farm, Tea Sorting House]

304
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:29,640
Hey, you.

305
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,160
Your farm isn't tiny, you know?

306
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:34,720
My legs are tired from all the walking.

307
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:38,800
You also didn't tell me
we'd be walking this much. Ow.

308
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:42,060
- It's good to see you, Boss.
- Hello.

309
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,480
You come here just in time.

310
00:14:43,740 --> 00:14:46,640
The kids and I have made
braised pork curry today.

311
00:14:46,660 --> 00:14:48,220
It's the Boss's favorite.

312
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:49,300
Please have a seat.

313
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:50,600
Thank you, Auntie Nong.

314
00:14:50,700 --> 00:14:52,340
I'll make sure to savor it once I'm free.

315
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,440
Right.

316
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,520
Who's that?

317
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:00,320
By the way, this is Saitharn.

318
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:02,640
Starting tomorrow,

319
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,440
he'll be working at the farm with us.

320
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:10,120
Please guide and take care of him.

321
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:13,200
Also,

322
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:15,400
please keep an eye on his behavior.

323
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,680
No problem, Boss.

324
00:15:17,820 --> 00:15:20,760
Mok and Saeng will have a new friend.

325
00:15:21,140 --> 00:15:23,360
Speaking of those two, where are they?

326
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:25,260
Pawn, come here.

327
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:26,030
Auntie!

328
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:27,000
There.

329
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:29,880
How many times have
I told you to call me 'Paula'?

330
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,280
Pawn' isn't a Gen Z name, is it?

331
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:34,200
I know. Go and bring them here.

332
00:15:34,220 --> 00:15:35,700
Bring the boys here.

333
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:37,920
Boss needs them to do something.

334
00:15:38,140 --> 00:15:39,080
This is your job.

335
00:15:39,420 --> 00:15:41,240
Why do we have to
waste our time walking to them?

336
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:43,540
Mok! Saeng!

337
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,560
Mok! Saeng! Come here!

338
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:50,120
Your mouth is full of food, isn't it?

339
00:15:50,140 --> 00:15:51,680
Where have you been slacking off, huh?

340
00:15:51,700 --> 00:15:53,660
Everyone has been helping prepare the food.

341
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:55,240
You guys are getting
too lazy at this point.

342
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:57,020
Auntie, look at his face.

343
00:15:57,560 --> 00:16:00,640
Okay, this is Saitharn.

344
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:03,340
I'd like you two to

345
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,760
show him the ropes

346
00:16:04,780 --> 00:16:06,820
since he'll be working with us tomorrow.

347
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,600
He probably doesn't know
how to work on the farm yet,

348
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:09,940
so guide him, okay?

349
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:11,320
Don't forget this.

350
00:16:11,340 --> 00:16:13,000
Anyway, please do continue
with your meal, everyone.

351
00:16:13,160 --> 00:16:15,160
It must have been very exhausting today.

352
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:17,500
Oh... I asked our workers to bring you

353
00:16:17,540 --> 00:16:18,920
some snacks and soft drinks.

354
00:16:19,060 --> 00:16:20,200
Feel free to knock yourselves out.

355
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:23,100
I'll take Saitharn to
his worker's housing first.

356
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:24,640
- I'll see you all later.
- Thank you.

357
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:28,440
Hey, you!

358
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:31,160
We haven't agreed for
me to be a worker yet.

359
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,120
Hey, you!

360
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:35,840
Where's the worker's housing?

361
00:16:36,280 --> 00:16:38,280
He seems like a strange guy, doesn't he?

362
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:41,940
What? You dare make that face?

363
00:16:42,620 --> 00:16:43,700
Gahh! You rascals!

364
00:16:43,720 --> 00:16:45,600
Where are you running off to?!
Get back here!

365
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,280
Where do you think you're going?!

366
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:00,320
Alright. We're here.

367
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,920
Your worker's housing.

368
00:17:10,619 --> 00:17:14,000
Isn't there one behind the cafeteria?

369
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,160
And...

370
00:17:16,359 --> 00:17:18,200
Why is mine so isolated from others'?

371
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:21,880
Just do as I say.

372
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:24,119
Starting today,

373
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:26,180
I am your boss.

374
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,400
Dictator.

375
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:28,240
Huh?

376
00:17:28,540 --> 00:17:30,360
No, nothing.

377
00:17:39,060 --> 00:17:40,440
Come on. This way.

378
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,000
Okay, fine.

379
00:17:44,940 --> 00:17:46,040
Better than staying with others...

380
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,480
Move out of the way, will you?

381
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:15,840
From now on, get up to work at 5 A.M.

382
00:18:15,860 --> 00:18:17,320
and finish work at 6 P.M.

383
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,560
You can have only one day off a month.

384
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:22,040
You must inform me before going anywhere.

385
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:24,100
You're not allowed to
leave the farm without notice.

386
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:26,280
And more importantly,
you must put your heart into your work.

387
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:29,140
Tell Saeng-La and Mok
if you need anything,

388
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:31,020
or you can come see me
at the main house.

389
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,600
It's less than 500 meters from here.

390
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:35,400
Your salary is 15,000 baht.

391
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:38,280
Pay me back however much
you can manage each month

392
00:18:38,580 --> 00:18:39,880
until the debt is cleared.

393
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,220
15,000 baht a month?

394
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:46,020
How many months do I have to work here

395
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:47,400
to clear the debt?

396
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:51,120
But if you want to finish
paying your debt sooner,

397
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:53,600
I guess you know

398
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:55,320
what you have to do.

399
00:18:58,280 --> 00:18:59,760
Another important note.

400
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,520
You must call me

401
00:19:04,380 --> 00:19:05,520
"Your Daddy."

402
00:19:06,420 --> 00:19:07,560
Are you out of your mind?!

403
00:19:08,140 --> 00:19:09,560
"Your Daddy," my ass!

404
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,160
Everyone has only one dad.

405
00:19:11,220 --> 00:19:12,420
That's the rule!

406
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:15,040
You are a worker under my supervision.

407
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:17,720
Thus, you have to call me...

408
00:19:19,800 --> 00:19:20,780
- Bo...
- Boss!

409
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:22,680
Boss!

410
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,840
Boss, Saitharn.

411
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,920
Auntie Nong told us
to bring you braised pork curry.

412
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:30,760
She's also included a banana in
coconut milk for you, Saitharn.

413
00:19:31,560 --> 00:19:33,240
As for Boss's, it's with Mok.

414
00:19:34,170 --> 00:19:35,440
Mm. Thank you very much.

415
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:37,960
Wait.

416
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,880
Why don't I get to have
a banana in coconut milk?

417
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:41,720
I don't know.

418
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,840
Oh, this might mean that

419
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:45,860
Saitharn is

420
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:47,920
Auntie Nong's next beloved boy.

421
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:51,200
As for you, Boss...

422
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:52,820
I guess you've been sidelined.

423
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:54,280
Hey, hey, hey...

424
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:58,440
Tomorrow, Saeng and I
will come to wake you up.

425
00:19:58,860 --> 00:20:01,040
Is there anything else you need?

426
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:04,860
Don't worry, Boss.

427
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:06,040
We've got this.

428
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:08,500
Who says I'm worried?

429
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:09,760
I'm not.

430
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:12,200
See you tomorrow morning, Saitharn.

431
00:20:12,230 --> 00:20:13,400
We have to go now.

432
00:20:18,120 --> 00:20:19,400
Be careful, or you'll spill it.

433
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,240
Thank you for driving me home.

434
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:37,140
No problem, Ms. Mueanphae.

435
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:40,560
By the way,

436
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,080
there seem to be a lot of guards here.

437
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,560
Oh.

438
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:45,840
My father said that

439
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:48,800
there would be guests from
other provinces coming to the vicinity.

440
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:51,140
That's probably why there are more guards.

441
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:52,640
Oh.

442
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:54,520
Boss Montri.

443
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,120
Yes.

444
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:58,600
But over these past years,

445
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,920
I've noticed that he has a regular guest.

446
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:03,360
He'd bring these many guards
whenever there's a visit.

447
00:21:03,620 --> 00:21:06,200
I can't help but wonder who it is

448
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:07,560
and how influential they are.

449
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:09,560
He hasn't introduced
this guest to us at all.

450
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:12,200
Even Manmuang doesn't know who they are.

451
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:13,700
I have to go now.

452
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:14,980
- Yes, Ms. Mueanphae.
- Thank you.

453
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:15,640
With pleasure.

454
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:27,680
Based on the intel gathered,

455
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:30,520
Phusangdao Farm is further
ahead than expected.

456
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:31,760
It's not just about the deals.

457
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,480
They're also stealing partners
right out from under us.

458
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,800
Whoever thinks they can push me out,

459
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:40,680
they'll know that I, Manmuang,
never go down without a fight.

460
00:21:41,140 --> 00:21:44,920
Given the situation, there's likely going to be
another round of negotiations with K Group.

461
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:47,080
Should we push to speed things up?

462
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,300
Push the negotiations forward immediately.

463
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:51,420
I want all the data on
my desk by tomorrow morning.

464
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:53,100
I expect the full report
to be ready when I wake up.

465
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:54,900
Don't even think about sleeping
until you have finished it.

466
00:21:55,220 --> 00:21:55,880
Understood.

467
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:08,280
Muang.

468
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,800
What did you get yourself into this time?

469
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,080
Uh, well...

470
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:21,680
Maple Syrup, the car that Dad gave me,

471
00:22:21,740 --> 00:22:23,840
got dented, and its paint scratched.

472
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:26,760
But don't worry about this.

473
00:22:26,860 --> 00:22:29,040
Sila has taken care of the payment,

474
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:30,200
but...

475
00:22:30,230 --> 00:22:32,240
can you keep this away from Dad?

476
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:33,560
Then, I...

477
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:35,040
- I'm sorry.
- Sila?

478
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,340
What does he have to do with this?

479
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:38,300
He crashed into your car?

480
00:22:38,320 --> 00:22:39,480
No, it's not like that.

481
00:22:40,560 --> 00:22:42,600
It was probably his new worker who did it.

482
00:22:42,780 --> 00:22:45,200
Sila came to take care of the mess,
so that has to be it.

483
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:47,040
His new worker?

484
00:22:48,780 --> 00:22:51,960
But Phusangdao Farm hasn't hired
any new workers in years.

485
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,560
Did Sila tell you

486
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:57,040
who the new worker was,
where they came from,

487
00:22:57,560 --> 00:22:59,240
or what position they held?

488
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,920
Um... He didn't tell me anything.

489
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:03,660
It seems like he was very new.

490
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,520
The guy didn't even seem
to be close to Sila,

491
00:23:07,660 --> 00:23:08,920
as if they were unacquainted.

492
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:12,000
I'm exhausted.

493
00:23:12,280 --> 00:23:14,040
I'm gonna go get changed now.

494
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:27,240
Who is this new worker at Phusangdao Farm?

495
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:29,000
Give me all of the details.

496
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:41,840
Saitharn!

497
00:23:41,860 --> 00:23:44,140
- Saitharn! It's time to get to work.
- Oh...

498
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:45,240
It's a new day!

499
00:23:59,550 --> 00:24:01,040
Oh.

500
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:06,720
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

501
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,000
Come on, Saitharn.

502
00:24:12,340 --> 00:24:13,680
A hat like that

503
00:24:13,900 --> 00:24:15,800
won't help you last half a day in the field.

504
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,560
It won't protect you from the sunlight.

505
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,360
Come on. Let's start here.

506
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:23,900
Watch closely, Saitharn.

507
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,960
Pick any tea leaves that look tender.

508
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,480
- And...
- Mok and Saeng!

509
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:31,120
Come to me for a moment.

510
00:24:31,930 --> 00:24:34,500
Help me carry the basket to
the Tea Sorting House.

511
00:24:34,520 --> 00:24:35,560
My back has given up.

512
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:37,400
Yes.

513
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,480
You two go and help them.

514
00:24:40,860 --> 00:24:42,860
I think I kind of understand
how this works now.

515
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,460
Don't worry.

516
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:45,240
- Alright.
- Okay.

517
00:25:05,780 --> 00:25:06,480
Hi.

518
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:07,280
Whoa!

519
00:25:22,440 --> 00:25:23,240
Ah!

520
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:24,280
Boss!

521
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:33,220
Aunt, look.

522
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:35,680
You're such a silly goose.

523
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,040
Are you sure you can do this?

524
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:41,600
How is he endearing?

525
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:43,200
I can't be bothered to take pity on him.

526
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,100
Alright, Koen.

527
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:48,140
I'll give you a load of this.

528
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,660
- Anything else?
- That's enough.

529
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:50,720
- Okay.
- Thank you.

530
00:25:51,740 --> 00:25:52,440
Alright.

531
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:57,160
What is this, Paula?!

532
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:59,080
Serve it properly, come on!

533
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:01,260
This is like serving air on my plate.

534
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:02,880
I served you based on your look.

535
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:04,300
You look totally sad,

536
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:06,000
so that's all you'll get.

537
00:26:06,240 --> 00:26:07,200
Fine.

538
00:26:15,260 --> 00:26:16,580
Hey, guys!

539
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:17,720
Look, look.

540
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,300
Who is Boss looking for?

541
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:31,160
Auntie.

542
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,560
Don't you think Boss is acting a bit weird?

543
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:36,460
He rarely comes to the farm.

544
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:38,600
Today, he has already
come here two or three times.

545
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:42,240
Oh, maybe...

546
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,560
he is dating someone here?

547
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:48,120
Ugh! Do you know anything, Auntie?

548
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,000
Wait, Faii!

549
00:26:50,380 --> 00:26:51,680
Could it be you?

550
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:53,000
Am I right?

551
00:26:53,400 --> 00:26:54,880
Don't let me find out myself.

552
00:26:55,300 --> 00:26:57,900
If it's anyone who will win his heart,

553
00:26:57,920 --> 00:27:00,220
it has to be me.

554
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:03,080
You're daydreaming. Don't be too nosy,

555
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:04,540
or else you'll stay single forever.

556
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:07,000
Auntie! You can't say that.

557
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:09,340
- Mm.
- I do want to date a guy.

558
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,560
Nonsense.

559
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,260
You can start picking
the tea leaves at dawn,

560
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:18,180
which is when they are still fresh

561
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,540
and covered in dew.

562
00:27:19,560 --> 00:27:21,140
The best ones are

563
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:24,260
the very top bud, along with
the two tender leaves right below it.

564
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:29,240
Use your thumb and index finger
to gently pinch the bud.

565
00:27:29,260 --> 00:27:30,280
Don't pull too hard,

566
00:27:30,340 --> 00:27:33,680
as it can deform the leaves
and harm the other plants.

567
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:40,360
Gently pinch the bud, right?

568
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:42,320
Gently pinch it...

569
00:27:46,860 --> 00:27:50,440
Once picked, place the tea leaves
into the bamboo basket.

570
00:27:50,720 --> 00:27:53,300
Try not to layer them too thickly,

571
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:54,840
and do not squeeze them,

572
00:27:54,860 --> 00:27:56,940
as this preserves their integrity

573
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:59,000
and prevents premature fermentation.

574
00:27:59,780 --> 00:28:02,880
Picking tea leaves isn't just about speed,

575
00:28:02,900 --> 00:28:05,320
but also about touch and timing.

576
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:09,380
The best time is
right before the sun gets too harsh,

577
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,540
as the leaves won't wither,

578
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:13,360
and will still be bursting
with their natural aroma.

579
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:18,960
Some things in life

580
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:23,840
also require touch and timing, don't they?

581
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,960
Tending to a tea farm

582
00:28:36,980 --> 00:28:38,780
requires understanding,

583
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:39,780
patience,

584
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:42,580
and time for the little things
that others would overlook,

585
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:44,280
much like how you nurture your own soul.

586
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:51,600
Thanks.

587
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:58,600
If you want to start picking tea leaves,

588
00:28:58,710 --> 00:29:01,180
sometimes all it takes is sincerity

589
00:29:01,200 --> 00:29:03,080
and a gentle touch with your fingertips.

590
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:12,240
Once picked, place the tea leaves
into the bamboo basket.

591
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:15,040
After picking

592
00:29:15,560 --> 00:29:17,400
the tea leaves,

593
00:29:17,720 --> 00:29:20,480
gently place them into the basket.

594
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:22,840
Gently.

595
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:35,400
Gosh!

596
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:38,280
When will you be done,
picking them this slow?

597
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:41,240
I pay you to work, not slack off.

598
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:45,840
You'd probably be done next year if
you kept up this pace for the whole field.

599
00:29:58,320 --> 00:29:59,120
And what is this?

600
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:00,680
You think this is it?

601
00:30:01,360 --> 00:30:02,000
Here.

602
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:04,120
I'll teach you.

603
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:09,840
Listen closely.

604
00:30:14,060 --> 00:30:15,120
When picking a bud,

605
00:30:15,220 --> 00:30:16,480
do it like this.

606
00:30:16,780 --> 00:30:18,620
This is where your index finger should be.

607
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:19,660
- See that?
- Mm.

608
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:21,600
What you did was snap its twig in half.

609
00:30:23,080 --> 00:30:24,200
Hey.

610
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:26,010
You are so heavy-handed.

611
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:27,760
Hey.

612
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:30,480
Listen up. I'm teaching here.

613
00:30:33,420 --> 00:30:35,280
If you want to pick
high-quality tea leaves,

614
00:30:35,560 --> 00:30:37,000
you have to pick them in the morning.

615
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:39,360
That's when the leaves
are soft and fragrant,

616
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:40,560
and they don't wither easily.

617
00:30:41,060 --> 00:30:43,320
It's okay if you pick them
in the afternoon.

618
00:30:43,700 --> 00:30:45,000
But the quality will drop.

619
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:49,440
I'll teach you how to
pick the leaves first.

620
00:30:51,520 --> 00:30:52,520
Do as I say.

621
00:30:54,340 --> 00:30:54,960
Here.

622
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:57,120
See?

623
00:31:00,720 --> 00:31:02,080
Now, give it a go.

624
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:07,000
There.

625
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:10,600
No, it's okay.

626
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,680
Not like that.

627
00:31:16,040 --> 00:31:16,760
See?

628
00:31:31,940 --> 00:31:32,840
Not too bad.

629
00:31:34,370 --> 00:31:36,320
It'd be great if you could
keep this up every day,

630
00:31:37,140 --> 00:31:38,720
so that no one will
have to instruct you.

631
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:40,720
Come on.

632
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,480
You don't have to instruct me

633
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:44,760
if you want to be this much of a poser.

634
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:45,900
Stop arguing.

635
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:49,080
I'm the Boss here!
You have to listen to what I say.

636
00:31:49,480 --> 00:31:50,240
Don't be stubborn!

637
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:51,680
Understood?

638
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:02,620
There.

639
00:32:02,780 --> 00:32:03,520
Put it on.

640
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:06,000
Or the sun will burn you alive.

641
00:32:06,740 --> 00:32:08,000
Even though it's tough here,

642
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:10,040
but we treat everyone well.

643
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:12,560
Whoa.

644
00:32:13,560 --> 00:32:16,120
You're truly a poser.

645
00:32:16,640 --> 00:32:17,240
Hey.

646
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:19,520
I can dock your pay, alright?

647
00:32:41,400 --> 00:32:42,500
- Whoa!
- Oh?!

648
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:43,360
Let's move!

649
00:33:08,900 --> 00:33:10,160
Quicker.

650
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:12,520
What?!

651
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,760
Are you not going to help me at all?

652
00:33:14,980 --> 00:33:16,000
It's heavy, you know?

653
00:33:16,660 --> 00:33:18,400
I've helped you by instructing you.

654
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:22,100
Don't frown this much
over carrying a basket.

655
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:24,200
Others' baskets are much heavier.

656
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:29,640
Hey.

657
00:33:30,360 --> 00:33:32,200
Keep your back straight.

658
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,600
What is it now?

659
00:33:34,800 --> 00:33:37,440
Why do you have to be
so fussy with these things?

660
00:33:37,780 --> 00:33:39,320
If your back ends up crooked,

661
00:33:39,340 --> 00:33:41,280
will you still think
this is just a minor issue, Saitharn?

662
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:44,400
Keep your back straight
when carrying a basket.

663
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:45,920
Make it a habit.

664
00:33:46,020 --> 00:33:47,760
It will keep the weight balanced

665
00:33:48,360 --> 00:33:49,720
and also make it feel lighter.

666
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:52,430
Mm.

667
00:33:52,980 --> 00:33:53,880
Understood?

668
00:33:54,600 --> 00:33:56,960
Now, head to the Tea Sorting House

669
00:33:57,060 --> 00:33:58,360
to get your basket weighed.

670
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:00,760
Yes, understood.

671
00:34:00,860 --> 00:34:03,440
I'll carry this heavy basket

672
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:06,200
and get in the line to weigh the leaves
as quickly as I can.

673
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:07,600
As for you,

674
00:34:07,740 --> 00:34:08,880
have a rest,

675
00:34:09,139 --> 00:34:10,080
wash your hands,

676
00:34:10,219 --> 00:34:13,400
take a shower, and chill out in
your room as much as you want.

677
00:34:17,120 --> 00:34:18,320
Your back, keep it straight.

678
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:19,199
Yeah.

679
00:34:30,460 --> 00:34:33,300
Of all the tea leaves you've picked,
these are the only ones that made the cut.

680
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:34,080
What?!

681
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:37,159
I picked the leaves all day,
but why only this much?

682
00:34:37,260 --> 00:34:39,000
My back is killing me here.

683
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,400
It's alright.

684
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:42,040
There's a first time for everything.

685
00:34:42,159 --> 00:34:43,679
Mok's first harvest

686
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:46,199
was so much worse than you.

687
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:49,320
Wait...

688
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:51,159
Why is your neck so red?

689
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:52,560
It's all red here.

690
00:34:53,639 --> 00:34:55,080
Please let me have a look.

691
00:34:55,679 --> 00:34:56,980
Woah, a stinging caterpillar!

692
00:34:57,970 --> 00:34:58,550
A singing caterpillar! No!

693
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:00,750
- Hey!
- Whoa!

694
00:35:07,280 --> 00:35:08,520
It's gone.

695
00:35:09,060 --> 00:35:11,320
Go and get him changed.

696
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:14,560
Saeng and Mok, take care of him.

697
00:35:15,300 --> 00:35:15,960
Go on.

698
00:35:17,300 --> 00:35:18,440
Auntie Nong,

699
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:21,900
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

700
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:23,060
It's alright.

701
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:24,580
We'll talk about it later.

702
00:35:24,600 --> 00:35:26,680
It's okay.

703
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:27,760
I'm really sorry.

704
00:35:28,080 --> 00:35:29,040
I'm so sorry.

705
00:35:29,980 --> 00:35:30,540
Go on.

706
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:31,900
- It's okay.
- Go now.

707
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:32,860
It's okay, Saitharn.

708
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:33,860
Let's go.

709
00:35:33,880 --> 00:35:35,100
It's this way, right?

710
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:35,820
Yes.

711
00:35:38,680 --> 00:35:39,280
Auntie.

712
00:35:40,100 --> 00:35:40,720
Auntie.

713
00:35:43,180 --> 00:35:44,960
Let me talk to you for a second.

714
00:35:45,210 --> 00:35:46,540
He's caused so much
trouble on the first day.

715
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:48,680
If he keeps working here,
he'll surely ruin our farm.

716
00:35:48,780 --> 00:35:52,080
But your favorite boy
can do no wrong, right?

717
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:54,680
Don't say that. He's not like that.

718
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:56,640
You never treat me as such.

719
00:35:58,020 --> 00:35:59,180
Oh, you.

720
00:36:00,260 --> 00:36:02,920
You're still going to take
my spot with that little space?

721
00:36:17,260 --> 00:36:18,360
How are you doing?

722
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:20,640
Itchy.

723
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:22,180
Here's a towel.

724
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:23,840
- Thank you.
- Right.

725
00:36:27,960 --> 00:36:29,440
Whoa!

726
00:36:29,660 --> 00:36:31,280
Your whole body is all red.

727
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:34,520
How are your legs doing?

728
00:36:34,540 --> 00:36:35,880
- Whoa, whoa.
- Saeng.

729
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:38,240
Giving him the medicine is enough.

730
00:36:41,080 --> 00:36:43,320
Don't scratch it or it'll get worse.

731
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,840
Here's your antihistamines.

732
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:47,660
I got it from the main quarter.

733
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:48,840
It'll get better once you take it.

734
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:51,920
By the way, for this afternoon,

735
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,280
about the vegetable patches,

736
00:36:53,420 --> 00:36:54,640
you can go later.

737
00:36:56,440 --> 00:36:59,120
Saeng and I will work there on your behalf.

738
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:01,400
Take the medicine and rest up.

739
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,040
And...

740
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,360
What about the tea leaves?

741
00:37:07,620 --> 00:37:09,760
Oh, it's okay.

742
00:37:09,940 --> 00:37:11,160
Don't think too much about it.

743
00:37:11,260 --> 00:37:13,680
Accidents can happen
at any given point here.

744
00:37:13,700 --> 00:37:15,040
Don't think too much of it.

745
00:37:16,080 --> 00:37:17,360
There was a worker

746
00:37:17,500 --> 00:37:20,020
who came across
a caterpillar on the first day

747
00:37:20,040 --> 00:37:22,000
and ran away like there was no tomorrow...

748
00:37:22,060 --> 00:37:23,800
They didn't come here for days.

749
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:25,000
Yeah, that's true.

750
00:37:25,140 --> 00:37:26,460
Someone like Paula

751
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,840
once fell into the canal behind the farm,

752
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:31,240
ruining her whole basket.

753
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:33,900
She was also staring at you harshly.

754
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:34,580
She needs to get a piece of this.

755
00:37:37,770 --> 00:37:39,120
There. You can smile now.

756
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:42,280
Saitharn, no need to worry.

757
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:44,180
Take your medicine and have a rest.

758
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:46,540
Then take another shower this evening.

759
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:47,680
As for this afternoon's work,

760
00:37:47,740 --> 00:37:51,140
both of us will work harder for your sake.

761
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:52,760
Huh?! What the hell?

762
00:37:52,980 --> 00:37:54,940
- Me too?
- Yes, you!

763
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:56,100
- Come.
- No

764
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:57,880
- Let's go!
- Woah

765
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:05,120
These kids are wild, aren't they?

766
00:38:10,620 --> 00:38:12,280
Ugh, Mok!

767
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:14,340
Double the work?

768
00:38:14,360 --> 00:38:16,080
You didn't even bother
discussing with me first.

769
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:24,300
Do it yourself. No chance I'm helping ya.

770
00:38:24,330 --> 00:38:26,180
You never help, though.

771
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:27,680
What? Jeez!

772
00:38:28,400 --> 00:38:30,680
Right, but I do sympathize with Saitharn.

773
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:32,720
He seems to feel terrible.

774
00:38:33,740 --> 00:38:35,480
I've made a lot of mistakes,
and you see that too, right?

775
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:37,800
I've never felt as terrible as he does.

776
00:38:38,480 --> 00:38:39,800
Am I actually...

777
00:38:40,740 --> 00:38:41,920
emotionless?

778
00:38:42,700 --> 00:38:44,240
There!

779
00:38:44,500 --> 00:38:46,500
See? You still feel it.

780
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:49,320
That's not what I meant!
Don't make me strike back.

781
00:38:51,180 --> 00:38:52,560
I'm just trying to say that

782
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:55,800
you and Saitharn
are two different people.

783
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:58,840
We've only known Saitharn for a day,

784
00:38:59,380 --> 00:39:01,080
so let's just take time
to get to know him.

785
00:39:01,620 --> 00:39:03,760
"Just take time to get to know him."

786
00:39:04,420 --> 00:39:07,400
Jeez, you're acting like
you're pursuing a girl.

787
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:10,320
You can't resist
that sweet look of his, can you?

788
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:13,320
Why? Are you jealous?

789
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,600
Jealous? Is the heat getting to you?

790
00:39:17,240 --> 00:39:18,800
No, I'm just saying that...

791
00:39:19,800 --> 00:39:21,800
Boss assigned us

792
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:23,640
to supervise Saitharn.

793
00:39:23,740 --> 00:39:25,740
That's why we had to wait for him
in front of the restroom

794
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:29,040
and hand him a towel for his hair?

795
00:39:30,060 --> 00:39:31,160
Don't act like you forgot.

796
00:39:31,460 --> 00:39:33,160
When you were stung
by that hairy caterpillar,

797
00:39:33,300 --> 00:39:35,520
you screamed for the whole farm to hear.

798
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:38,400
When I finally got you to shower...

799
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:41,240
Darn, how tired I was.

800
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:44,080
You didn't get any rashes, though.

801
00:39:46,140 --> 00:39:47,740
You've got some damn thick skin.

802
00:39:48,180 --> 00:39:50,400
Wow, what about when you were a kid

803
00:39:50,420 --> 00:39:52,600
and got a hairy caterpillar
on your peepee?!

804
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:55,620
You were jump-hugging
Auntie Nong so freaking tight.

805
00:39:55,640 --> 00:39:57,120
Whose is the size of a caterpillar?

806
00:39:57,180 --> 00:39:59,880
Mine is an anaconda!

807
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:01,080
Whoa...

808
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,200
But I haven't seen
that anaconda in a long time.

809
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,220
- Can I get a peek, Mok?
- Whoa!

810
00:40:05,240 --> 00:40:06,560
Get your mind out of the gutter, Saeng!

811
00:40:07,060 --> 00:40:10,000
Hottie, let me see your anaconda!

812
00:40:11,220 --> 00:40:14,020
Goodness, Miss, I've already told you

813
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:15,720
that I would select the fabrics for you

814
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:17,860
so that it would be ready for you to use.

815
00:40:17,880 --> 00:40:19,880
Selecting these with you
is a lot more fun, Nanny.

816
00:40:20,020 --> 00:40:21,780
If I had done this on my own,

817
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,360
I wouldn't have known

818
00:40:23,700 --> 00:40:25,340
where these fabrics

819
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:26,800
I've seen at home were from.

820
00:40:26,900 --> 00:40:29,360
Once I got into it, I realized that

821
00:40:29,500 --> 00:40:32,600
not all of our fabrics
are from Chiang Rai.

822
00:40:33,180 --> 00:40:35,680
There are many good ones
from our highlands.

823
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:38,120
That's correct, Miss.

824
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:40,980
Some of these are
from my hometown in the highlands.

825
00:40:42,380 --> 00:40:45,720
Take a look.
Is there anything that you particularly like?

826
00:40:47,540 --> 00:40:51,160
I'll make you a beautiful outfit from it,

827
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:54,000
like the silky princess dress
you wore when you were little.

828
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,020
Do you remember that, Miss?

829
00:40:56,040 --> 00:40:57,680
Oh, the yellow one, wasn't it?

830
00:40:57,700 --> 00:40:58,960
Of course, I remember it.

831
00:40:59,100 --> 00:41:01,800
My tulle skirt was much more dramatic
than anyone back then.

832
00:41:04,940 --> 00:41:06,000
Look at this.

833
00:41:07,640 --> 00:41:11,080
I'm so proud of you, Miss.

834
00:41:12,040 --> 00:41:13,600
This little hand

835
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:15,760
that always helped me

836
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:17,600
go through the fabrics

837
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:19,440
and select them.

838
00:41:20,500 --> 00:41:21,560
Right now,

839
00:41:22,800 --> 00:41:25,000
you can do it all by yourself.

840
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:28,500
Ever since

841
00:41:29,440 --> 00:41:31,300
you went abroad to study fashion,

842
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:34,800
I've always been praying

843
00:41:35,340 --> 00:41:38,360
for only good things to come your way.

844
00:41:41,820 --> 00:41:43,040
I'm happy

845
00:41:43,060 --> 00:41:45,120
that you're able to do what you love.

846
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:49,080
Seeing you happy,

847
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:51,360
I'm also happy, Miss.

848
00:41:56,600 --> 00:42:00,520
By the way, you haven't told me
what you're gonna make use of these.

849
00:42:00,620 --> 00:42:01,640
Oh,

850
00:42:01,860 --> 00:42:04,020
here, let me show you.

851
00:42:08,320 --> 00:42:09,920
- Put this away for me.
- Yes, sir.

852
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:12,520
Nanny,

853
00:42:12,940 --> 00:42:14,360
anything to eat?

854
00:42:15,380 --> 00:42:17,640
There are green curry
and fish cakes, Mr. Manmuang.

855
00:42:21,980 --> 00:42:23,480
Go make some shrimp fried rice
for me, would you?

856
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:25,800
Why green curry all week?

857
00:42:32,140 --> 00:42:33,000
Muang!

858
00:42:33,360 --> 00:42:35,440
Didn't you see that Nanny
was helping me with something?

859
00:42:37,760 --> 00:42:38,480
Something?

860
00:42:40,460 --> 00:42:41,440
What thing?

861
00:42:43,820 --> 00:42:46,000
What are you gonna splurge
your family's money on now?

862
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:50,480
Phae,

863
00:42:50,940 --> 00:42:53,200
if you truly want to do something useful,

864
00:42:54,400 --> 00:42:56,080
help with the family's business,

865
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:58,540
not just dress pretty

866
00:42:58,560 --> 00:43:00,560
and drive to see Sila every day.

867
00:43:01,840 --> 00:43:03,780
There are so many things
that Dad wants you to do,

868
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:06,360
so why have I never seen you
show any interest in those?

869
00:43:08,020 --> 00:43:10,800
I've never said
I want to be in charge of Dad's tea farm.

870
00:43:11,580 --> 00:43:12,960
I don't want a job like you.

871
00:43:13,610 --> 00:43:14,800
I am not you,

872
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:17,520
and I will never be like you.

873
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:21,800
Really?

874
00:43:23,800 --> 00:43:25,560
Is it not because

875
00:43:26,810 --> 00:43:28,480
you don't wanna cross the line with Sila?

876
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:32,960
Yes.

877
00:43:35,280 --> 00:43:36,320
Yes, Muang.

878
00:43:37,480 --> 00:43:39,320
Never once
do I want to come across as his enemy.

879
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:41,040
I want to work with him.

880
00:43:41,560 --> 00:43:42,520
Do you know why?

881
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:44,640
Because he sees that I'm determined,

882
00:43:46,560 --> 00:43:47,520
unlike you

883
00:43:48,640 --> 00:43:49,640
who sees nothing but yourself.

884
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:50,640
Mueanphae.

885
00:43:51,020 --> 00:43:51,840
Mueanphae!

886
00:44:07,780 --> 00:44:09,040
Right, Sila.

887
00:44:09,140 --> 00:44:11,100
I'm thinking about traveling tomorrow

888
00:44:11,120 --> 00:44:13,120
since I'll have to prepare
the fabrics there, anyway.

889
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:17,320
Plus, I'm starting
to get sick of the condo.

890
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:19,900
I can't wait to find inspiration there.

891
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:21,660
Are you actually sick of the condo,

892
00:44:21,680 --> 00:44:23,820
or your nights out at clubs?

893
00:44:23,840 --> 00:44:25,000
No.

894
00:44:25,240 --> 00:44:26,600
It's not like that.

895
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:29,480
I'm just so sick
and tired of traffic jams.

896
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:32,400
I want to live in nature like you do.

897
00:44:32,960 --> 00:44:34,200
Speaking of...

898
00:44:35,060 --> 00:44:36,320
we need to talk about you.

899
00:44:36,940 --> 00:44:39,880
The other night,
you just disappeared mid-text.

900
00:44:40,240 --> 00:44:41,980
Did you...

901
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:44,440
Hey, hey, hey, don't look at me like that.

902
00:44:45,440 --> 00:44:46,320
It's just...

903
00:44:48,640 --> 00:44:50,480
Uh... Forget it.

904
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:52,340
Let's talk about you.

905
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:55,320
Let me just say
that as soon as you arrive,

906
00:44:55,880 --> 00:44:59,480
there will be a surprise for you
the moment you set foot in Chiang Rai.

907
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:01,940
So get ready, little one.

908
00:45:03,360 --> 00:45:05,360
Someone like you planning a surprise for me?

909
00:45:05,560 --> 00:45:06,280
What?

910
00:45:07,560 --> 00:45:08,880
Do you mean a pro like me?

911
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:11,300
Right, so what time is your flight?

912
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:12,680
I'll have Chakkrit waiting to pick you up.

913
00:45:12,820 --> 00:45:14,680
Hey, there's no need.

914
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:15,920
I'm super chill.

915
00:45:16,400 --> 00:45:18,520
I'll just... find my own ride

916
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:20,820
in case I want to stop
for a walk in the city.

917
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:22,120
Are you sure, Gale?

918
00:45:22,480 --> 00:45:23,400
Keep me posted.

919
00:45:23,800 --> 00:45:25,240
Sure thing.

920
00:45:25,640 --> 00:45:28,220
- I'm super chill.
- Gale, I have to go. I'll be back.

921
00:45:28,240 --> 00:45:29,360
Okay.

922
00:45:37,700 --> 00:45:39,080
Whoa! Saeng.

923
00:45:40,980 --> 00:45:42,440
You've been looking for it for so long.

924
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:44,760
If Saitharn had been bitten by a snake,
wouldn't he be a goner by now?

925
00:45:45,720 --> 00:45:48,320
Do you think
it's that easy to find an ointment?

926
00:45:48,800 --> 00:45:50,420
Come here! Help me look.

927
00:45:56,560 --> 00:45:58,560
Hey, what are you two doing here?

928
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:05,360
Did something happen to someone?

929
00:46:06,400 --> 00:46:09,840
Saitharn was stung
by a hairy caterpillar, Boss.

930
00:46:10,160 --> 00:46:11,860
We've already given him allergy meds,

931
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:14,380
but... there are still rashes,

932
00:46:14,400 --> 00:46:16,000
so we're looking for an ointment.

933
00:46:18,300 --> 00:46:20,300
Then, you two go rest.

934
00:46:20,680 --> 00:46:22,020
I'll find him one.

935
00:46:22,040 --> 00:46:22,880
- Yes, Boss.
- Yes, Boss.

936
00:46:22,900 --> 00:46:23,920
Come here.

937
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:09,960
This has already been a bad day,

938
00:47:10,920 --> 00:47:13,240
and I still have to deal
with spookiness tonight?

939
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:37,320
Hey, hey, hey, you!

940
00:47:38,760 --> 00:47:39,480
Uh...

941
00:47:39,660 --> 00:47:40,540
You old man!

942
00:47:40,560 --> 00:47:41,380
Sorry!

943
00:47:41,400 --> 00:47:42,380
What are you doing?!

944
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:43,280
I...

945
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:45,440
Uh...

946
00:47:53,600 --> 00:47:55,160
Mok said you were stung
by a hairy caterpillar,

947
00:47:55,720 --> 00:47:57,040
so I'm bringing you some medication.

948
00:47:58,120 --> 00:47:58,920
Mm,

949
00:47:59,760 --> 00:48:01,320
but I'm fine now.

950
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:04,680
Just leave it out by the door.

951
00:48:05,880 --> 00:48:07,880
Then, I'll hang it by the door handle.

952
00:48:08,420 --> 00:48:09,540
Don't forget to apply it.

953
00:48:13,400 --> 00:48:14,780
Oh, and...

954
00:48:14,800 --> 00:48:17,100
People here aren't really used to
someone dressed so revealingly

955
00:48:17,120 --> 00:48:18,880
like Bangkok people do.

956
00:48:18,980 --> 00:48:20,120
Put some clothes on.

957
00:48:20,820 --> 00:48:23,600
You just barged in out of nowhere!

958
00:48:23,900 --> 00:48:25,640
This is my personal space.

959
00:48:25,930 --> 00:48:27,280
I can do anything I want, right?

960
00:48:29,640 --> 00:48:30,400
Also...

961
00:48:33,040 --> 00:48:35,840
please forget what you saw.

962
00:48:37,160 --> 00:48:38,880
I can forget what I saw,

963
00:48:40,080 --> 00:48:43,160
but I can still remember
what happened that night so vividly.

964
00:48:51,120 --> 00:48:52,720
It was just a one-night stand!

965
00:48:52,900 --> 00:48:54,480
We go our separate ways
after the night ends!

966
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:57,040
I'm not hooking up
with the same person twice.

967
00:48:58,120 --> 00:48:59,840
Good. That's clear.

968
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:01,630
I've just realized

969
00:49:01,910 --> 00:49:03,720
what Gen Zers are like.

970
00:49:09,720 --> 00:49:11,040
It's time for you to go.

971
00:49:12,160 --> 00:49:13,400
I'm going to bed soon.

972
00:49:14,380 --> 00:49:16,680
I have to wake up
to work off a debt I owe someone.

973
00:49:18,440 --> 00:49:20,960
Then, if you need something,
come see me at the main quarter.

974
00:49:21,600 --> 00:49:23,720
Feel free to tell me
if you can or cannot handle it.

975
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:27,220
Whoa, hey!

976
00:49:27,240 --> 00:49:29,480
You have the audacity
to ask if I can handle it?

977
00:49:29,620 --> 00:49:32,740
Let me tell you something:
ever since I was born,

978
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:35,200
my parents never even
let me touch a broom.

979
00:49:35,620 --> 00:49:37,380
Here I am, fresh out of college

980
00:49:37,400 --> 00:49:38,940
and not obligated to get into the workforce,

981
00:49:38,960 --> 00:49:40,960
but because of you!

982
00:49:41,180 --> 00:49:44,200
You forced me
to get my first job against my will.

983
00:49:47,720 --> 00:49:49,200
Hey, you!

984
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:52,000
Mr. Sila, are you listening?!

985
00:50:01,120 --> 00:50:01,880
Hey!

986
00:50:22,080 --> 00:50:23,520
This old man is pretty...

987
00:52:14,920 --> 00:52:18,020
Tea harvesting isn't merely about speed,

988
00:52:18,040 --> 00:52:20,520
but it is also about touch and rhythm.

989
00:52:21,080 --> 00:52:22,700
The best time to do it

990
00:52:22,720 --> 00:52:24,540
is before the sun gets too harsh.

991
00:52:24,560 --> 00:52:25,700
The tea leaves won't wilt

992
00:52:25,720 --> 00:52:28,560
and will still be naturally aromatic.

993
00:52:32,880 --> 00:52:34,380
Tending to a tea farm

994
00:52:34,400 --> 00:52:36,180
requires proper understanding,

995
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:37,140
patience,

996
00:52:37,160 --> 00:52:39,980
and taking time with small things
that other people overlook,

997
00:52:40,000 --> 00:52:41,720
just like how you nurture your own heart.

998
00:52:48,480 --> 00:52:52,340
Use your thumb and index finger
to slowly pinch the tip of the leaf.

999
00:52:52,360 --> 00:52:53,420
Don't pull it too hard

1000
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:54,900
because the leaf could lose its shape

1001
00:52:54,920 --> 00:52:56,800
and damage the remaining leaves.

1002
00:52:57,840 --> 00:52:58,820
After harvesting...

1003
00:52:58,840 --> 00:53:00,440
- take it to...
- Boss. Hello there.

1004
00:53:01,220 --> 00:53:02,880
Oh, hello.

1005
00:53:17,880 --> 00:53:19,000
Come on, Saitharn.

1006
00:53:22,600 --> 00:53:24,260
If you look deeper into him,

1007
00:53:24,280 --> 00:53:26,820
Boss is kind, not at all stern.

1008
00:53:26,840 --> 00:53:29,880
He takes good care
of the workers on the farm.

1009
00:53:30,720 --> 00:53:32,520
The weather here is super nice.

1010
00:53:32,540 --> 00:53:34,360
Just lounging around is nice enough.

1011
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:35,780
When summer arrives,

1012
00:53:35,800 --> 00:53:37,520
come play with us in the water.

1013
00:53:38,440 --> 00:53:41,120
When that time comes,
I might not be here anymore.

1014
00:53:42,000 --> 00:53:43,960
Are you rushing back to your partner?

1015
